    <!-- Best Practices -->
    <section style="margin-bottom: 48px;">
      <h2 style="font-family: 'Sora', sans-serif; font-size: 28px; font-weight: 800; color: #f1f5f9; margin-bottom: 24px; letter-spacing: -0.04em;">Mailto link best practices</h2>
      <div class="insight-grid" style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, minmax(0, 1fr)); gap: 20px;">
        <div class="insight-card">
          <div style="font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 12px;">&#9993;</div>
          <h3 style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; color: #f1f5f9; margin-bottom: 8px;">Keep it short</h3>
          <p style="font-size: 14px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); line-height: 1.6;">Long mailto URLs can break in some email clients. Keep your subject and body concise, or use the body as a starting prompt rather than a full message.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="insight-card">
          <div style="font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 12px;">&#128279;</div>
          <h3 style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; color: #f1f5f9; margin-bottom: 8px;">Use clear link text</h3>
          <p style="font-size: 14px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); line-height: 1.6;">Instead of "Click here," use descriptive text like "Email our sales team" or "Request a demo." It helps both users and search engines understand the link's purpose.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="insight-card">
          <div style="font-size: 24px; margin-bottom: 12px;">&#128272;</div>
          <h3 style="font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; color: #f1f5f9; margin-bottom: 8px;">Consider spam</h3>
          <p style="font-size: 14px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); line-height: 1.6;">Exposing email addresses in HTML can attract spam bots. For high-traffic pages, consider using a contact form alongside your mailto link.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section style="max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto 48px;">
      <h2 style="font-family: 'Sora', sans-serif; font-size: 28px; font-weight: 800; color: #f1f5f9; margin-bottom: 8px; letter-spacing: -0.04em;">Frequently asked questions</h2>
      <p style="font-size: 15px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.4); margin-bottom: 24px;">Everything you need to know about mailto links.</p>

      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">What is a mailto link?<svg class="faq-chevron" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg></button>
        <div class="faq-a">A mailto link is an HTML hyperlink that opens the user's default email client with pre-filled fields. Instead of linking to a webpage, it uses the mailto: protocol to trigger an email compose window with the recipient, subject, body, CC, and BCC already filled in.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Do mailto links work on mobile?<svg class="faq-chevron" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes. Mailto links work on iOS (opens Mail or Gmail), Android (opens Gmail or your default mail app), and all desktop browsers. The device's default email client opens automatically.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Can I pre-fill the email body?<svg class="faq-chevron" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes. The body parameter lets you pre-fill the message content. This generator handles all the URL encoding automatically, including line breaks and special characters.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Is there a character limit?<svg class="faq-chevron" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg></button>
        <div class="faq-a">URLs should stay under 2,000 characters for broad compatibility. This generator shows a live character count so you can monitor length. For longer templates, keep the body short and let the user fill in the details.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">Can I add multiple recipients?<svg class="faq-chevron" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes. Separate multiple email addresses with commas in the To, CC, or BCC fields. For example: user1@example.com,user2@example.com.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q">How do I use this on my website?<svg class="faq-chevron" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7" /></svg></button>
        <div class="faq-a">Click "Copy HTML Code" and paste it into your website's HTML. The link will render as clickable text. You can style it with CSS like any other anchor tag.</div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(31,41,55,0.6), rgba(17,24,39,0.6)); border: 1px solid rgba(75,85,99,0.5); border-radius: 24px; padding: 48px; text-align: center; margin-bottom: 48px;">
      <h2 style="font-family: 'Sora', sans-serif; font-size: 28px; font-weight: 800; color: #f1f5f9; margin-bottom: 12px; letter-spacing: -0.04em;">Automate your entire email workflow</h2>
      <p style="font-size: 16px; color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5); max-width: 480px; margin: 0 auto 24px; line-height: 1.6;">This tool builds one link. <a href="/voiceai" style="color: #10b981; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600;">Naurra</a> sends, reads, replies, and organizes your entire inbox with one voice command.</p>
      <div style="display: flex; gap: 12px; justify-content: center; flex-wrap: wrap;">
        <a href="/" style="padding: 14px 28px; background: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981, #059669); color: white; border-radius: 12px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(16,185,129,0.3);">Try Naurra Free</a>
        <a href="/tools" style="padding: 14px 28px; background: rgba(255,255,255,0.06); border: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.1); color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); border-radius: 12px; text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600;">More free tools</a>
      </div>
